{
  "texts": [
    "To further analyze the generative behavior of ENMA and Zebra, we visualize PCA projections of feature representations extracted by a CNN trained on ground truth data.",
    "As shown in fig. 22, ENMA's samples (orange) closely align with the real data (blue), indicating that the generated trajectories remain well-covered within the training distribution.",
    "In contrast, Zebra exhibits a large number of outliers that fall outside the support of the real data distribution.",
    "This mismatch suggests poorer calibration and lower fidelity to the training dynamics, which aligns with the lower FPD and precision scores reported in table 17.",
    "These findings confirm ENMA's ability to generate physically plausible and distributionally consistent trajectories."
  ]
}